[gd_scene load_steps=56 format=3 uid="uid://di7plimb8je4i"]

; Intentional GREYBOX PLACEHOLDER. Painterly art is quarantined under godot/_quarantine/;
; this scene keeps the project runnable on primitives while Path A is blocked out.
;
; EXPLORABLE-ROUTE BLOCKOUT (2026-06-22, promoted from gizmo-level-design lab with user
; approval — canon/spawn-hearth.yaml + canon/route-exploration.yaml). The spine is a JOURNEY,
; not a corridor (canon: "the route is pilgrimage, not hallway"). South→north (warm→cold):
;   Hearth (spawn z+17, one road out) → discernment FORK → West/East approaches (+ a West
;   cache spur) → Landmark gear-henge (z-12, both rejoin) → Trial arena (surroundable) → Sanctuary pocket
;   (z-30, with a loopback) → cold Beacon dais far north (z-42, NOT visible from spawn) →
;   horizon spire (the wider Meridian). LevelZones markers track these beats for the baker.
;   `DesignProbe_ExposureRanks` = the non-shipping exposure-rank legend (delete before ship;
;   canon: pressure is diegetic, no on-screen meter). Blockout meshes carry no
;   `footprint_meters`, so game_controller ignores them as obstacles: visual read only, the
;   sim still owns the walkable footprint (locked mechanic 6).
;
; COLLISION LAYER (2026-06-22, user granted collision-box rights): `LevelCollision`
; (StaticBody3D) holds one CollisionShape3D per SOLID scenery piece — hearth/sanctuary walls,
; henge monument + ring pillars, trial + east obstacles, west cache, brazier, sanct form,
; beacon, the reachable spire. The PLAYER (Gizmo CharacterBody3D, move_and_slide, no gravity)
; now physically collides: the hearth's single north egress is physically TRUE, and the henge
; reads as a monument you path AROUND. Gold-path tiles / alcove platforms / dais carry NO
; collider (walkable; Gizmo rides y=0). Meshes still carry no `footprint_meters`, so the
; SIM/enemies still ignore them (locked mechanic 6 intact) — ADR-0014 sim-obstacle
; registration (footprint_meters + placement_role + collision_shape_count) is the next
; integration step, deferred so this stays a player-collision pass, not an enemy-nav change.
;
; DESIGN-SYSTEM HANDOFF (2026-06-22): each material's pole+register binding for gizmo-design-system
; integration is the lab witness `witnesses/material-pole-handoff.md` (canon
; handoff_declares_pole_per_exposure_order). Poles split at the TRIAL: LIVING (hearth / fork / henge /
; west loop / sanctuary) vs HOLLOWED (trial cover / cold approach / Dormant Beacon / decayed scenery);
; Sparks/caches = violet; the Beacon ships DORMANT (teal-drain, scarce-teal core-spark is the
; DS-animated active state). DesignProbe_ExposureRanks = delete-before-ship (non-shipping legend).

